Responsibilities:
- Handle purchase orders and follow up with suppliers on delivery schedule;
- Carry out administrative work and clerical support for the department;
- Handle other ad hoc project as assigned

Requirements:
- Higher Diploma or above;
- 1-2 years of working experience in supplement or beauty is preferred;
- Detail oriented with good numeric sense and strong negotiation and analytical skills;
- Able to work under pressure with good multi-tasking skills;
- Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
- Proficiency in MS Office, including MS Word, MS Excel;
- Immediate available is highly preferred

Duties

Support the Operations in matching supply & demand of the project material-wise;
Handle material sourcing & vendor selection of construction materials;
Process quotation comparison / analysis, conduct price negotiation and make recommendation;
Prepare procurement contract document, purchase order etc;
Manage in-house purchasing system;
Prepare monthly reports & inventory control, work closely with internal parties to keep track & monitor inventory movement & purchasing needs;
Involve in the tendering & planning process;
Ad hoc duties as assigned.

 Requirements

Certificate in Purchasing & Supply Chain Management or Construction related discipline is preferred;
3 years solid purchasing experience in construction industry;
Experience in managing in-house purchasing system;
Good problem-solving, negotiating, organization, interpersonal & communication skills;
Mature, independent, integrity, proactive, co-operative and positive working attitude;
A strong team player and able to work under pressure;
Ability to multi-task & prioritize with minimum supervision;
Proficient in MS Office (Word & Excel)
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese.



Interested parties please send your full resume with date available, present & expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".


