(Ref: PM (FO) 2022-01-14)

Responsibilities:
lead the Procurement Team to manage the purchasing functions of the University, outsourced on-campus catering services and business services including general insurance, office supplies and appointed travel agents for business trips;
develop effective procurement and sourcing strategies and formulate cost-saving initiatives;
formulate, review and implement policies and procedures on procurement for continuous improvement;
manage the procurement activities and obtain the best value-for-money options in all aspects of goods and services required for the University’s operation and resolve any contractual disputes;
liaise with the service providers of on-campus catering outlets on service quality, environment and hygiene, and pricing matters; and
manage and regularly review the general insurance arrangement with the appointed insurance broker to ensure adequate coverage for risk mitigation.

Applicants should:
possess a bachelor’s degree or above in Procurement, Business Administration, or related disciplines, preferably with professional qualifications (e.g. CIPS or equivalent);
have at least 10 years’ relevant work experience in sizeable organisations, of which at least 5 years should be at managerial level;
possess solid experience and knowledge in the procurement process and contract management;
possess good leadership and interpersonal skills to work effectively with requisition units, suppliers and other teams of the Finance Office;
have business acumen, strong communication, presentation and problem-solving skills and be able to perform tasks of great diversity requiring considerable independent analysis and evaluation; and
have good command of written and spoken English and Chinese.
Applicants with work experience in the higher education sector / public sector will be an advantage.


Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested applicant should visit this link https://recruit.hsu.edu.hk/ and apply on or before 30 January 2022.  The University reserves the right not to fill the position in this exercise.
Applicants who are not invited to an interview within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful.  All information received will be treated in strict confidence, and the data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  The Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request.
The Hang Seng University of Hong Kong, incorporated in Hong Kong with limited liability by guarantee, is an equal opportunity employer.

Responsibility
- Execute regular purchasing duties, e.g. PO processing, price negotiation, vendor sourcing, etc.;
- Co-ordinate with other departments and suppliers in the purchasing scope of work;
- Monitor the service, quality, price, on-time delivery and reliability of the suppliers.
- Perform other duties as assigned.


Requirement
Academic Qualification: Bachelor Degree holder or above;
Field of Study: Logistic / Supply Chain Management / Manufacturing / Engineering / Business Administration or other relevant discipline;
Years of Experience: 1 - 3 years of related working experience;
*Fresh graduate will also be considered.
- Knowledgeable and hands-on experience in SAP & MS Office.
- Effective communication skill with good command of written and spoken English & Chinese.

Fringe Benefit
- Double Pay;
- Incentive Bonus;
- 5-days Work;
- 12-19 days annual leave;
- Medical, Dental & Life Insurance Scheme.

Application Method
Interested parties please click "APPLY NOW" or send your application with the title & expected salary to HK Human Resources via Application E-mail.

