Our client is a well-established food distributor representing a number of prestigious Japanese FMCG/food brands and having good market share in Hong Kong. 
In line with their business development, they now require a responsible and detail-minded talent to join their team as Merchandising Officer.  The caliber with less years of relavant working experiences will be considered as Assistant Merchandising Officer.

 Responsibilities:

Handle merchandising & sourcing matters, such as purchasing, suppliers, inventory;
Responsible for logistics/warehouse operation and stock-take operation regularly;
Coordinate in purchasing operation with Japan or overseas offices;
Handle shipping cost calculation, quality control on products importing to Hong Kong;
Assist in marketing events & regular stock operations

Requirements:

Tertiary education in buying/purchasing or business relating discipline;
At least 5 years working experience in purchasing/product control, especially in Food & Beverage / Retailing industry;
Good command in spoken English and Cantonese;
Excellent language literacy (both spoken and written) in Japanese is highly preferable;
Proficient in MS Office, Sage Accpac knowledge an advantage;
Detailed-minded and good problem solving skills with strong sense of responsibility

Responsibilities:

Responsible for performing market research on the up-coming fashion trend;
Assemble and execute plans for seasonal brand assortment and OTB in order to meet the company’s business objective;
Products sourcing and sell-thru analysis;
Liaise with suppliers on order placing efficiency and ensure appropriate levels of stock of designated product categories are maintained;
Allocate merchandises and coordinate with shops and warehouse to smooth the stock replenishment issue;
Work closely with operations, visual merchandising team and other counterparts to maximize sales performance of responsible category;
Cultivate and maintain partnership relationship with suppliers

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree holder
Min. 4 years’ apparel / footwear buying experience
Solid experience in branded merchandise buying, store replenishment, merchandise consolidation and product management is a must
Strong business sense with excellent negotiation, interpersonal, numerical and analytical skills
Fluent in spoken and written English, Chinese and Mandarin
Proficient in MS Excel (Pivot Table, VLookup and other formula functions)
Willing to travel
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Buyer

Interested parties please send your resume with current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".


