Key Responsibilities

Provide daily support to team members throughout the merchandising cycles;

Responsible for gathering and inputting data into the system as well as ensuring order details accuracy before issuing purchase orders to suppliers;
Perform samples measurement according to company’s quality standard requirements and identify quality issues at an early stage;
Prepare individual product style and quality requirement packages to Quality Assurance & Quality Control (“QA & QC”) team for inspection;
Provide general clerical assistance to team members throughout the merchandising cycles from the arrangement of courier, general samples packing to filing;
Provide other ad-hoc support to the team.

Requirements



Completion of higher secondary school or diploma studies ideally with fashion or textile educational background;
Minimum 2 years’ relevant experience in the garment industry and preferably with knowledge in Woven/Outdoor items;
Ability to work under pressure and tight deadlines with a proactive and positive attitude;
Good communication skills, well-organized and attentive to details;
Experience in order follow up ranged from sample development to bulk production;
Proficiency in MS Excel, Word, and Outlook Express;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (fluency in Cantonese and Mandarin).

What we offer

Excellent development and career growth opportunity;
Multinational and open-minded work environment;
Competitive remuneration and benefits.

Job Duties:

The scope of your job responsibilities will include but is not limited to the following:

Comprehend petty cash management and efficiency analysis to ensure proper cashflow statements;
Maintain and monitor procurement and supply management in relation to current suppliers, credit term maintenance, and marginal cost evaluations;
Assist in sourcing items as they relate to all functions of the restaurants including but not limited to food, drink, structural, and miscellaneous goods;
Assistant accounting and human resource divisions with Owlsome group as needed at the instruction and guidance of the general manager;
Fulfil roster and shift duties across multiple restaurants as needed as the instruction and guidance of the general manager;
Assist in coordination of activities and guidelines set out by the general manager in relation to marketing, community, or group related activities as it relates to any or all of our restaurant locations;
Work hand in hand with shop managers in the daily operations of the business to help provide timely information, proper maintenance, and effective leadership as outlined and instructed by the General Manager of Owlsome restaurants;
In addition to the duties which this job normally entails, you may from time to time be required to undertake additional or other duties as necessary to meet the needs of the Company’s business;
Actively participate and support outside office company-held events occasionally;
Any company events activities as required.
